{
  "stem": "7358.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had made up my mind that I will never live sort of in the Diaspora any longer at the time.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I wanted to go only to Israel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my family wanted to go to the United States.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My uncle, my uncle and my aunt and their two sons wanted to go to the United States.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] I decided that I have-- that I will separate from them at that point, because I made up my mind that I will only go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I joined the-- it was sort of like an orphanage home, but it was ran by, by Israelis from-- it was actually ran by people, survivors, from, from the uprising in the, in the Warsaw ghetto.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But they were all connected with Israeli organizations.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the sole purpose of this home was to gather single children-- you know, orphans-- and, and, and try to bring them to Israel.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I joined this place.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was a little older than the average child.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was, at that time, approximately, 18 years old, or 17-- close to 18.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I spoke Hebrew fluently.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So immediately, I was [? up in ?] classes and we started to teach the children Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I liked this life very well.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And at the time, meanwhile, the war ended.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as you know, the British were, were controlling Palestine at the time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Was a British mandate.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And because of oil interests and political interests, they went along with the Arabs as to limit the immigration of Jews to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- but since the group that I belonged to was mostly younger children, and, and most of them orphans, we were able to get-- to go to Israel in a legal manner.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
